Step 1: Identify Total Liabilities at the end of the reporting period.  
• Accounts Payable = 6,600,000.00  
• Taxes Payable = 1,428,630.43  
• Total Liabilities = 6,600,000.00 + 1,428,630.43 = 8,028,630.43  

Step 2: Identify Total Assets at the end of the reporting period.  
• Total Assets = 39,772,748.32  

Step 3: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio using the formula:  

  Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 8,028,630.43 / 39,772,748.32  
  ≈ 0.202 (rounded to three decimal places)  

Rounded to two decimal places, the Debt to Asset Ratio is approximately 0.20.

Thus, the answer is:
